%h1 Unread Books

%h2 Low-Hanging Fruit
%p books which have relatively low page counts, but haven't yet been read. If you're looking for Thomas Mann or James Joyce, look elsewhere.

%table
	-@fruit.each do |book|
		%tr
			%td #{book.title}
			%td #{book.pages}
			%td= link_to 'Show', book
			%td= link_to 'Edit', edit_book_path(book)


%p What classifies a book as "unread?" In general, it's a book that is in the catalog which has no associated reading.

%table
	-@books.each do |book|
		%tr
			%td #{book.title}
			%td= link_to 'Show', book
			%td= link_to 'Edit', edit_book_path(book)